0,1024,512+67,67,376,376_PJAdblSocialShare-Gradientoverlay-twitter-largeasin-0to60,TopLeft,0,0_PJAdblSocialShare-AudibleLogo-Medium,TopLeft,490,223_OU01_ZBLISTENING%20ON,483,152,55,450,AudibleSansMd,32,255,255,255.jpg"},"thesaurus_subject_keywords":["la_confidential"],"title":"The Hobbit"},{"asin":"B0099RKRTY","asset_details":[],"authors":[{"asin":"B000ARC6KA","name":"J. R. R. Tolkien"}],"available_codecs":[{"enhanced_codec":"LC_64_22050_stereo","format":"Enhanced","is_kindle_enhanced":true,"name":"aax_22_64"},{"enhanced_codec":"LC_32_22050_stereo","format":"Enhanced","is_kindle_enhanced":true,"name":"aax_22_32"},{"enhanced_codec":"LC_64_44100_stereo","format":"Enhanced","is_kindle_enhanced":true,"name":"aax_44_64"},{"enhanced_codec":"LC_128_44100_stereo","format":"Enhanced","is_kindle_enhanced":true,"name":"aax_44_128"},{"enhanced_codec":"aax","format":"Enhanced","is_kindle_enhanced":false,"name":"aax"}],"category_ladders":[{"ladder":[{"id":"18574426011","name":"Literature & Fiction"},{"id":"18574449011","name":"Classics"}],"root":"Genres"},{"ladder":[{"id":"18580606011","name":"Science Fiction & Fantasy"},{"id":"18580607011","name":"Fantasy"},{"id":"18580615011","name":"Epic"}],"root":"Genres"}],"content_delivery_type":"MultiPartBook","content_type":"Product","format_type":"unabridged","has_children":true,"is_adult_product":false,"is_listenable":true,"is_preview_enabled":false,"is_purchasability_suppressed":false,"is_vvab":false,"issue_date":"2012-10-09","language":"english","merchandising_summary":"Inspired by The Hobbit and begun in 1937, The Lord of the Rings is a trilogy that J.R.R. Tolkien created to provide \"the necessary background of history for Elvish tongues\". From these academic aspirations was born one of the most popular and imaginative works in English literature. The...","narrators":[{"name":"Rob Inglis"}],"product_images":{"1000":"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81PJmZlkTSL._SL1000_.jpg"},"publication_datetime":"2012-10-09T05:00:00Z","publication_name":"The Lord of the Rings","publisher_name":"Recorded Books","publisher_summary":"<p>Inspired by <i>The Hobbit</i> and begun in 1937, <i>The Lord of the Rings</i> is a trilogy that J.R.R. Tolkien created to provide &quot;the necessary background of history for Elvish tongues&quot;. From these academic aspirations was born one of the most popular and imaginative works in English literature. </p> <p><i>The Fellowship of the Ring</i>, the first volume in the trilogy, tells of the fateful power of the One Ring. It begins a magnificent tale of adventure that will plunge the members of the Fellowship of the Ring into a perilous quest and set the stage for the ultimate clash between the powers of good and evil. </p> <p>In this splendid, unabridged audio production of Tolkien's great work, all the inhabitants of a magical universe – hobbits, elves, and wizards – step colorfully into life. Rob Inglis' narration has been praised as a masterpiece of audio.</p>","rating":{"num_reviews":3010,"overall_distribution":{"average_rating":4.826645670227148,"display_average_rating":"4.8","display_stars":5.0,"num_five_star_ratings":58810,"num_four_star_ratings":6349,"num_one_star_ratings":322,"num_ratings":67313,"num_three_star_ratings":1464,"num_two_star_ratings":368},"performance_distribution":{"average_rating":4.769424231246437,"display_average_rating":"4.8","display_stars":5.0,"num_five_star_ratings":49547,"num_four_star_ratings":7458,"num_one_star_ratings":304,"num_ratings":59642,"num_three_star_ratings":1921,"num_two_star_ratings":412},"story_distribution":{"average_rating":4.856671025718406,"display_average_rating":"4.9","display_stars":5.0,"num_five_star_ratings":53426,"num_four_star_ratings":4588,"num_one_star_ratings":204,"num_ratings":59646,"num_three_star_ratings":1139,"num_two_star_ratings":289}},"release_date":"2012-10-09","runtime_length_min":1147,"series":[{"asin":"B009CFOEGK","sequence":"1","title":"The Lord of the Rings","url":"/pd/The-Lord-of-the-Rings-Audiobook/B009CFOEGK"}],"sku":"BK_RECO_006156","sku_lite":"BK_RECO_006156","social_media_images":{"facebook":"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/51eVNlqfveL._SL10_UR1600,800_CR200,50,1200,630_CLa%7C1200,630%7C51eVNlqfveL.jpg%7C0,0,1200,630+82,82,465,465_PJAdblSocialShare-Gradientoverlay-largeasin-0to70,TopLeft,0,0_PJAdblSocialShare-AudibleLogo-Large,TopLeft,600,270_OU01_ZBLISTENING%20ON,617,216,52,500,AudibleSansMd,30,255,255,255.jpg","ig_bg":"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/51eVNlqfveL._SL200_BL80_UR1080,2160.jpg","ig_static_with_bg":"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/51eVNlqfveL._SL200_BL80_UR1080,2160_CLa%7C1080,2160%7C51eVNlqfveL.jpg%7C0,0,1080,2160+288,614,500,500_PJAdblSocialShare-Gradientoverlay-Radial,TopLeft,0,0_PJAdblSocialShare-AudibleLogo-Small,TopLeft,290,461_ZBLISTENING%20ON,290,410,52,500,AudibleSansMd,34,255,255,255_ZBThe%20Fellowship%20of%20the%20Ring,290,1183,52,500,AudibleSansSm,32,255,255,255_ZBJ.%20R.%20R.%20Tolkien,290,1247,52,500,AudibleSansRg,28,255,255,255.jpg","ig_sticker":"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71UyRin7-TL._CLa%7C614,913%7C51eVNlqfveL.jpg%7C0,0,614,913+70,79,471,473_FMpng_PJAudible-logo-dk,BottomLeft,70,-100_ZAThe%20Fellowship%20...,70,560,65,500,AudibleSansSm,42,54,54,54_ZAby%20J.%20R.%20R.%20Tolkien,70,640,52,517,AudibleSansRg,32,0,0,0.png","twitter":"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/51eVNlqfveL._SL10_UR1600,800_CR200,50,1024,512_CLa%7C1024,512%7C51eVNlqfveL.jpg%7C0,0,1024,512+67,67,376,376_PJAdblSocialShare-Gradientoverlay-twitter-largeasin-0to60,TopLeft,0,0_PJAdblSocialShare-AudibleLogo-Medium,TopLeft,490,223_OU01_ZBLISTENING%20ON,483,152,55,450,AudibleSansMd,32,255,255,255.jpg"},"subtitle":"Book One in The Lord of the Rings Trilogy","thesaurus_subject_keywords":["la_confidential"],"title":"The Fellowship of the Ring"},{"asin":"B002V1A2B8","asset_details":[],"authors":[{"asin":"B000ARC6KA","name":"J. R. R. Tolkien"}],"available_codecs":[{"enhanced_codec":"format4","format":"Format4","is_kindle_enhanced":false,"name":"format4"},{"enhanced_codec":"LC_128_44100_stereo","format":"Enhanced","is_kindle_enhanced":true,"name":"aax_44_128"},{"enhanced_codec":"mp444128","format":"Enhanced","is_kindle_enhanced":true,"name":"mp4_44_128"},{"enhanced_codec":"aax","format":"Enhanced","is_kindle_enhanced":false,"name":"aax"}],"category_ladders":[{"ladder":[{"id":"18574426011","name":"Literature & Fiction"},{"id":"18574449011","name":"Classics"}],"root":"Genres"},{"ladder":[{"id":"18580606011","name":"Science Fiction & Fantasy"},{"id":"18580607011","name":"Fantasy"},{"id":"18580614011","name":"Dramatizations"}],"root":"Genres"},{"ladder":[{"id":"18580606011","name":"Science Fiction & Fantasy"},{"id":"18580607011","name":"Fantasy"},{"id":"18580615011","name":"Epic"}],"root":"Genres"}],"content_delivery_type":"SinglePartBook","content_type":"Product","editorial_reviews":["For those who find the books too long-winded and the films too noisy, this is the perfect way to assimilate the myth and magic of Middle-earth"],"format_type":"unabridged","has_children":false,"is_adult_product":false,"is_listenable":true,"is_preview_enabled":false,"is_purchasability_suppressed":false,"is_vvab":false,"issue_date":"2007-09-05","language":"english","merchandising_summary":"With its first broadcast on BBC Radio 4 on March 8, 1981, this dramatised tale of Middle Earth became an instant global classic. It boasts a truly outstanding cast including Ian Holm (as Frodo), Michael Hordern (as Gandalf), Robert Stephens (as Aragorn), Bill Nighy (as Sam Gamgee) and John Le...","narrators":[{"name":"Peter Woodthorpe"},{"name":"Ian Holm"},{"name":"Robert Stephens"},{"name":"Michael Hordern"},{"name":"Bill Nighy"},{"name":"John McAndrew"},{"name":"David Collings"},{"name":"Douglas Livingstone"},{"name":"Full Cast"}],"product_images":{"1000":"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/514I5nYNocL._SL1000_.jpg"},"publication_datetime":"2007-09-05T15:33:00Z","publication_name":"BBC Radio’s The Lord of the Rings","publisher_name":"BBC Digital Audio","publisher_summary":"<p>With its first broadcast on BBC Radio 4 on March 8, 1981, this dramatised tale of Middle Earth became an instant global classic. It boasts a truly outstanding cast including Ian Holm (as Frodo), Michael Hordern (as Gandalf), Robert Stephens (as Aragorn), Bill Nighy (as Sam Gamgee) and John Le Mesurier (as Bilbo).<br /><br />Brian Sibley's famous adaptation has been divided into three corresponding parts, with newly-recorded beginning and end narration by Ian Holm, who now stars as Bilbo in the feature films based on <i>The Lord of the Rings</i>.<br /><br />Part One, <i>The Fellowship of the Ring</i>, introduces us to Frodo Baggins. With his uncle Bilbo having mysteriously disappeared, Frodo finds himself in possession of a simple gold ring that has great and evil power. It is the Ruling Ring, taken long ago from the Dark Lord, Sauron, who now seeks to possess it again. Frodo must do everything he can to prevent this, and with the help of Gandalf the wizard and a band of loyal companions he begins a perilous journey across Middle-earth. Sauron's Black Riders are on their trail as they travel to Rivendell, attempt to cross the snow-swept Misty Mountains and, in desperation, enter the terrifying Mines of Moria.<br /><br /><br />&copy;2018 BBC Studios Distribution Ltd (P)2018 BBC Studios Distribution Ltd</p>","rating":{"num_reviews":304,"overall_distribution":{"average_rating":4.495789995047053,"display_average_rating":"4.5","display_stars":4.5,"num_five_star_ratings":2937,"num_four_star_ratings":588,"num_one_star_ratings":154,"num_ratings":4038,"num_three_star_ratings":245,"num_two_star_ratings":114},"performance_distribution":{"average_rating":4.532557407989934,"display_average_rating":"4.5","display_stars":4.5,"num_five_star_ratings":2357,"num_four_star_ratings":447,"num_one_star_ratings":107,"num_ratings":3179,"num_three_star_ratings":193,"num_two_star_ratings":75},"story_distribution":{"average_rating":4.6876376218936775,"display_ave